<body>
    <h1>Emerging Standards for Immunizations</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>A working space to capture and reflect ideas and projects relate=
d to using FHIR and other emerging standards to<span>&nbsp;support</span><s=
pan> immunization interoperability and/or the modernization of immunization=
 information systems (IIS) to address unmet needs and/or improve processes.=
 </span>Topics are grouped to reflect their status relative to the <a href=
=3D"https://www.immregistries.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">American Immunization Registry Association</a> (AIRA) efforts to track an=
d foster immunization community collaboration, in partnership with the CDC:=
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
 <li><a href=3D"#EmergingStandardsforImmunizations-emerging">Emerging Topic=
s and Standards</a>: Prioritized topics where AIRA is actively working to u=
nderstand and <span style=3D"color:#333333;">document the business case for=
 a new standard/specification, based on information-gathering and immunizat=
ion community feedback.</span></li>
 <li><a href=3D"#EmergingStandardsforImmunizations-emerged">Emerged Standar=
ds</a>: Standards where work on developing, refining, or promoting the adop=
tion of specifications is or could be underway through sponsored efforts.</=
li>
 <li><a href=3D"#EmergingStandardsforImmunizations-parked">Parked</a>: Idea=
s for new standards/specifications.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"EmergingStandardsforImmunizations-SlideDecksandPresentations">Sli=
de Decks and Presentations</h1>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"781922f0-7ac3-4157-b35c-e6c514b421fb"><a href=3D"https://=
repository.immregistries.org/resource/navigating-emerging-standards-a-struc=
tured-approach/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Navigating Emergi=
ng Standards: A Structured Approach</a>, 2024, AIRA National Meeting Presen=
tation</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"13508601-bde6-4a21-9e8d-34c6aaaa402b"><a href=3D"https://=
repository.immregistries.org/resource/aira-discovery-session-emerging-stand=
ards-1/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Emerging Standards</a>, 2=
024 AIRA Discovery Session</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"170e0d90-03d8-4987-a5ff-905573210d29"><a href=3D"https://=
repository.immregistries.org/resource/fhiring-up-the-future-of-iis/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">FHIRing up the Future of IIS</a>, 2023,=
 AIRA National Meeting Presentation</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"6ab5ce32-59c6-482b-a5e6-2061732ea4d3"><a href=3D"https://=
repository.immregistries.org/resource/aira-discovery-session-emerging-stand=
ards/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Emerging Standards</a>, 201=
8 AIRA Discovery Session</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"EmergingStandardsforImmunizations-emergingEmergingTopicsandStanda=
rds"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"EmergingStandardsforImmun=
izations-emerging"></span>Emerging Topics and Standards</h1>
<p>Topics in the Monitor, Gather, and Start Stages. These represent priorit=
y topics where there is an effort to understand the need/opportunity and to=
 foster sponsored efforts to develop draft specifications. As part of the A=
IRA/CDC Emerging Standards initiative, AIRA primarily focuses on topics in =
this category, with a target of ~8 in Monitor, ~4 in Gather, and ~2 in Star=
t.</p>
